Manages steno stroke mechanics for count-expansion; a count bank "floats" by merging its keys into a single sub-stroke and re-rendering in canonical English steno order when a construct's count is non-zero. Example: `STKWR-PBGS/-FLT` with 3 params becomes `STKWR-PBGS/AOFLT`.

Canonical single-stroke order is `# | S T K P W H R | A O * E U | F R P B L G T S D Z`. The hyphen separates right-bank keys only when there is no middle (vowel or `*`); with a middle present, no hyphen.

The module re-exports two core abstractions: `bank` handles count-driven merging and stroke arithmetic (`CountBank`, `apply_count`, `merge_strokes`, `subtract_strokes`), and `keys` handles parsing and rendering (`parse_stroke`, `render_stroke`, `StrokeKeys`, `KeySet`). Both files are domain-specific; understand their names first.